result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathan E. Tipton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+) [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 10:32am [mo]
Defendant Nathan E. Tipton in court with Attorney Anthony Flitcroft.   ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of "Guilty" entered; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

The Court discloses, under SCR 60.04 that in the Court's former capacity as Jefferson County  Assistant District Attorney,  ADA Wambach did prosecute Mr. Tipton. The Court does not feel that any disqualification or recusal is needed.

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel

The Court withholds sentence and places Mr. Tipton on Probation for 3 years, with conditions: 
--to undergo assessment, treatment, and counseling as required by the Agent
--to obtain/maintain employment or education program as approved by the Agent
--to comply with all Family Court Orders regarding child support
--to make all child support payments on time
--to make all payments on arrearages according to the Child Support orders
--to advise Child Support Enforcement Agency of any employment or address change within 48 hours of such change
--within five days Mr.Tipton is to report to the Child Support Enforcement Agency: Room 219 of the Jefferson County Courthouse, 311 S. Center Avenue in Jefferson WI, to complete a case management meeting 
--to pay costs of $268 plus the 250 DNA surcharge
--to pay subpoena fees in the amount of $33
--not to leave State of Wisconsin without Court approval
--All payments toward child support and arrearages are to be paid through:  Wisconsin Support Collection Trust Fund, Box 74200, Milwaukee WI 53274-0200 (not through the Department of Corrections)

The Court does NOT require Mr. Tipton to provide a DNA sample, as he has already provided one. 
The Court grants 0 days credit
